about.summary: Collection of convenient functions for common statistical computations, which are not directly provided by R's base or stats packages. This package aims at providing, first, shortcuts for statistical measures, which otherwise could only be calculated with additional effort (like standard errors or root mean squared errors). Second, these shortcut functions are generic (if appropriate), and can be applied not only to vectors, but also to other objects as well (e.g., the Coefficient of Variation can be computed for vectors, linear models, or linear mixed models; the r2()-function returns the r-squared value for 'lm', 'glm', 'merMod' or 'lme' objects). The focus of most functions lies on summary statistics or fit measures for regression models, including generalized linear models and mixed effects models. However, some of the functions also deal with other statistical measures, like Cronbach's Alpha, Cramer's V, Phi etc.

name: r-sjstats
raw_recipe:
{% set version = '0.16.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-sjstats
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: sjstats_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/sjstats_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/sjstats/sjstats_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 2249f3b68b8540ccc79fa52c1f23b9105f082a52f8e7f67a33efabf4cb1f6a07

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  skip: true  # [win32]
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
    - r-matrix
    - r-bayesplot
    - r-broom >=0.4.5
    - r-coin
    - r-crayon
    - r-dplyr >=0.7.1
    - r-emmeans
    - r-glmmtmb >=0.2.2.0
    - r-lme4 >=1.1_12
    - r-lmtest >=0.9_34
    - r-magrittr
    - r-modelr
    - r-nlme
    - r-prediction
    - r-purrr >=0.2.2
    - r-pwr
    - r-rlang
    - r-sandwich >=2.3_4
    - r-sjlabelled >=1.0.11
    - r-sjmisc >=2.7.3
    - r-tibble >=1.3.3
    - r-tidyr >=0.7.0
    - r-tidyselect
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
    - r-matrix
    - r-bayesplot
    - r-broom >=0.4.5
    - r-coin
    - r-crayon
    - r-dplyr >=0.7.1
    - r-emmeans
    - r-glmmtmb >=0.2.2.0
    - r-lme4 >=1.1_12
    - r-lmtest >=0.9_34
    - r-magrittr
    - r-modelr
    - r-nlme
    - r-prediction
    - r-purrr >=0.2.2
    - r-pwr
    - r-rlang
    - r-sandwich >=2.3_4
    - r-sjlabelled >=1.0.11
    - r-sjmisc >=2.7.3
    - r-tibble >=1.3.3
    - r-tidyr >=0.7.0
    - r-tidyselect

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('sjstats')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('sjstats')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/strengejacke/sjstats, https://strengejacke.github.io/sjstats
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Collection of convenient functions for common statistical computations, which are
    not directly provided by R's base or stats packages. This package aims at providing,
    first, shortcuts for statistical measures, which otherwise could only be calculated
    with additional effort (like standard errors or root mean squared errors). Second,
    these shortcut functions are generic (if appropriate), and can be applied not only
    to vectors, but also to other objects as well (e.g., the Coefficient of Variation
    can be computed for vectors, linear models, or linear mixed models; the r2()-function
    returns the r-squared value for 'lm', 'glm', 'merMod' or 'lme' objects). The focus
    of most functions lies on summary statistics or fit measures for regression models,
    including generalized linear models and mixed effects models. However, some of the
    functions also deal with other statistical measures, like Cronbach's Alpha, Cramer's
    V, Phi etc.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'  # [unix]
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}\R\share\licenses\GPL-3'  # [win]

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
    - ccwang002
